'''''Amara Kaaviyam''''' ({{lit|Immortal Masterpiece}}) is a 1981 [[Tamil language|Tamil-language]] Indian feature film directed by Amirtham and produced by Vishwanatham Combines. It stars [[Sivaji Ganesan]], [[Sripriya]] and [[Madhavi (actress)|Madhavi]] in the lead roles.<ref>{{cite web|title=Amara Kaaviyam Vinyl LP Records|url=http://musicalaya.net/imgviewer.php?mod=lpcovers/39/3/1/1|publisher=musicalaya|accessdate=24 April 2014}}{{Dead link|date=May 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> The film was a remake of the [[Hindi]] film ''[[Muqaddar Ka Sikandar]]''.

== Cast ==

*[[Sivaji Ganesan]]
*[[Sripriya]]
*[[Madhavi (actress)|Madhavi]]
*[[Nagesh]]
*[[Major Sundarrajan]]

== Production ==
''Amara Kaaviyam'' is a remake of the [[Hindi]] film ''[[Muqaddar Ka Sikandar]]''. Sivaji Ganesan was chosen to reprise the role originally played by [[Amitabh Bachchan]], while his son [[Prabhu (actor)|Prabhu]] was to have reprised the role originally played by [[Amjad Khan (actor)|Amjad Khan]], in what would have been his debut film. Because friends of Ganesan felt the bloodshed between these two characters would not be appreciated by the audience, Prabhu could not play the role.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/Prabhu-is-ready-to-play-baddie/article14386225.ece|title=Prabhu is ready to play baddie|last=Vasudevan|first=K. V.|date=4 June 2016|work=[[The Hindu]]|access-date=14 August 2018|language=en-IN|issn=0971-751X}}</ref>

== Soundtrack ==
The film's original soundtrack was composed by [[M.S. Viswanathan]], while the lyrics were penned by [[Kannadasan]] & [[Vaali (poet)|Vaali]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.raaga.com/tamil/album/Amarakaviyam-songs-T0000996 |title=Amarakaviyam songs |website=''[[Raaga.com]]'' |access-date=2019-06-06}}</ref>

